What if I told you there’s a hidden island paradise just 1 hour away — and you can do it all under 30-40k? 👀🌴

Say hello to Bintan Island, Indonesia — a peaceful escape from the hustle of Singapore and a perfect 2-day add-on to your itinerary!

Here’s the breakdown: 
🛬 Round-trip flights to Singapore: Under ₹20K (I booked mine via @SkyScanner.india - if you are still not aware, it’s one of the easiest apps to compare flights and I always find some great deals in there)

🚤 Ferry to Bintan: 1-hour ride, round trip ~₹8K
🛂 Visa on Arrival (for Indians): Just ₹1500
🏖️ Resort stay: Starts at ₹10K per night (luxury feels!)
🌿 Activities: Mangrove Forest, ATV, water rides, temples — all under ₹10K
🍴 Food: Budget ₹5-6K for 2 days || depending on how fancy you want to go. 

It’s basically Singapore’s Goa — but way calmer and more scenic 😍 😍❤️
If you’re planning a trip to Singapore and want this dreamy 2-day extension — this is your sign to visit Bintan, Indonesia. Technically you cover 2 countries in 1 go. 

Comment ‘Bintan’ and I’ll DM you the full plan (with flight options too!) 💌📍

Would you add this EXPERIENCE to your Bucketlist? 😍❤️

This is located in Jordan and the place is called The Dead Sea. 

The Dead Sea is one of a kind sea in the world where you cannot sink. It’s 430m below the sea level and 10x saltier than ocean water. This is the reason why there is no marine life in here and the dense water makes it impossible to sink and you just float in here. 

Not just that, the mud and the sea salt is filled with minerals and it can solve most of your skin issues and health issues - but you need to apply it more often to cure things out and people stay here for months because of this 😍❤️

Just an E-Visa from Delhi and you will be able to enjoy this country on your next INTERNATIONAL TRIP

📌📌 SAVE this POST for your future travel plans//if you are into luxury shopping. 

Never pay the pay price until and unless you are really eyeing on a specific product//collection. 

Most of the people who are around you or are buying these goods are smart buyers and they do most of their shopping, just when they are travelling. 

I mostly do this and I feel it’s a great saving hack for someone who really wants to shop: 

If you are travelling to the UK -

1. Check Bicester Village near London. They have some amazing deals on different brands and you will be able to get quite a few things there. There is no tax refund in London anymore so that’s a con now. 

If you are travelling to EUROPE (you also get additional tax refunds so that’s a plus too) 

1. La Vallee Village Paris 

2. La Roca Village, Barcelona 

3. Serravalle - Milan (another great stop for your shopping needs) 

4. Noventa di Piave near Venice 

5. Designer outlet Parndorf, near Vienna 

Check which country you are visiting and find outlet malls near you :) 

This is shot in La Roca, Barcelona. 

The big ones are majorly in Paris, Spain and Italy along with London. 

Let me know your hacks in the comments below and I would love to know more 👯‍♀️❤️

If this helped you; do give me a follow and I would like to make content like these.

Charles & Keith at Singapore Airport 🇸🇬 is a SHOPPER’S PARADISE! 💃👜

If you’re a fashion lover and happen to be at Changi Airport, DO NOT skip the Charles & Keith store!
Why? Because this iconic Singaporean brand is priced way lower in its home country — and the airport store is next-level amazing 😍

✨ I got a pair of stunning heels for just INR 2,500 and a super cute wallet for INR 1,800 — legit steals!
💸 In India, the same heels retail for INR 9,000 and the wallets go for INR 4,000+ — no kidding.

🛍️ The collection at Changi is also updated, well-stocked, and has exclusive styles. And since it’s duty-free, you’re getting unbeatable deals + quality in one go!

🔁 Pro Tip: If you have a layover in Singapore, make sure you plan some time for a shopping sprint here — it’s totally worth it!

Have you been to Changi Airport before? Did you shop at Charles & Keith? Let’s chat in the comments! 💬👇
